{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:sirach.32",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 32,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 32 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.32.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:1",
      "text": "Have they made thee ruler? be not lifted up: be among them as one of them.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.32.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:2",
      "text": "Have care of them, and so sit down, and when thou hast acquitted thyself of all thy charge, take thy place:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.32.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:3",
      "text": "That thou mayst rejoice for them, and receive a crown as an ornament of grace, and get the honour of the contribution.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.32.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:4",
      "text": "Speak, thou that art elder: for it becometh thee,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.32.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:5",
      "text": "To speak the first word with careful knowledge, and hinder not music.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.32.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:6",
      "text": "Where there is no hearing, pour not out words, and be not lifted up out of season with thy wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.32.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:7",
      "text": "A concert of music in a banquet of wine is as a carbuncle set in gold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.32.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:8",
      "text": "As a signet of an emerald in a work of gold: so is the melody of music with pleasant and moderate wine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.32.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:9",
      "text": "Hear in silence, and for thy reverence good grace shall come to thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.32.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:10",
      "text": "Young man, scarcely speak in thy own cause.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.32.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:11",
      "text": "If thou be asked twice, let thy answer be short.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.32.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:12",
      "text": "In many things be as if thou wert ignorant, and hear in silence and withal seeking.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.32.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:13",
      "text": "In the company of great men take not upon thee: and when the ancients are present, speak not much.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.32.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:14",
      "text": "Before a storm goeth lightning: and before shamefacedness goeth favour: and for thy reverence good grace shall come to thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.32.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:15",
      "text": "And at the time of rising be not slack: but be first to run home to thy house, and there withdraw thyself, and there take thy pastime.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.32.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:16",
      "text": "And do what thou hast a mind, but not in sin or proud speech.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.32.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:17",
      "text": "And for all these things bless the Lord, that made thee, and that replenisheth thee with all his good things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.32.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:18",
      "text": "He that feareth the Lord, will receive his discipline: and they that will seek him early, shall find a blessing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.32.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:19",
      "text": "He that seeketh the law, shall be filled with it: and he that dealeth deceitfully, shall meet with a stumblingblock therein.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.32.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:20",
      "text": "They that fear the Lord, shall find just judgment, and shall kindle justice as a light.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.32.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:21",
      "text": "A sinful man will flee reproof, and will find an excuse according to his will.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.32.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:22",
      "text": "A man of counsel will not neglect understanding, a strange and proud man will not dread fear:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.32.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:23",
      "text": "Even after he hath done with fear without counsel, he shall be controlled by the things of his own seeking.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.32.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:24",
      "text": "My son, do thou nothing without counsel, and thou shalt not repent when thou hast done.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.32.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:25",
      "text": "Go not in the way of ruin, and thou shalt not stumble against the stones: trust not thyself to a rugged way, lest thou set a stumblingblock to thy soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.32.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:26",
      "text": "And beware of thy own children, and take heed of them of thy household.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.32.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:27",
      "text": "In every work of thine regard thy soul in faith: for this is the keeping of the commandments.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.32.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:28",
      "text": "He that believeth God, taketh heed to the commandments: and he that trusteth in him, shall fare never the worse.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
